  "prompt": "Can someone screenshot a snap after I block them?",
  "response": "If you block someone on Snapchat, they will no longer be able to see your stories, send you snaps, or interact with you in any way through the app. However, if they had already viewed a snap or a story of yours before you blocked them, they could potentially take a screenshot of that content while it was still visible to them. Once you block them, they cannot see anything you post or interact with you anymore.",
